# auth-contract@1 (frontend): the Privy app ID. Without this set, AuthProvider renders the app
# unauthenticated (no PrivyProvider mount) — the auth seam stays at its fail-closed default (no
# token), so owner-scoped calls (e.g. deployAgent) fire WITHOUT an Authorization header rather
# than fabricating one; the login UI is simply skipped. The "never fires unauthenticated" guarantee
# comes from wiring components/auth/AuthGate around the owner-scoped action, plus the backend's
# 401-before-any-side-effect boundary.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=
